{"title_page": "Toshiharu Morinaga", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Toshiharu Morinaga\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Toshiharu Morinaga\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1982|2|23}}\n|birth_place=[[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|height={{Height|m=1.78}}\n|position=[[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub=\n|clubnumber=\n|youthyears1=|youthclubs1=[[Kawasaki Frontale]]\n|years1=2001|clubs1=[[Tokyo Verdy]]|caps1=0|goals1=0\n|years2=2002|clubs2=[[FC Shinjuku]]|caps2=|goals2=\n|years3=2003|clubs3=[[Shenzhen Ruby F.C.|Shenzhen Jianlibao]]|caps3=|goals3=\n|years4=2003|clubs4=[[Qingdao Hailifeng F.C.|Qingdao Aokema]]|caps4=|goals4=\n|totalcaps=|totalgoals=\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n|medaltemplates=\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Toshiharu Morinaga'''|\u68ee\u6c38 \u654f\u6625|Morinaga Toshiharu|born February 23, 1982}} is a former [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player.\n\n==Playing career==\nMorinaga was born in [[Tokyo]] on February 23, 1982. He joined [[J1 League]] club [[Tokyo Verdy]] in 2001. In 2002, he moved to [[FC Shinjuku]]. In 2003, he moved to China and played for [[Shenzhen Ruby F.C.|Shenzhen Jianlibao]] and [[Qingdao Hailifeng F.C.|Qingdao Aokema]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.geocities.co.jp/Athlete-Sparta/2322/ma2.html]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morinaga, Toshiharu}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football people from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:J1 League players]]\n[[Category:Tokyo Verdy players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in China]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n{{Japan-footy-midfielder-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Toshiharu Morinaga\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Toshiharu Morinaga\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1982|2